{"doc":{"isMarkdown":false,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"Using the progressbar role","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/Accessibility/ARIA/ARIA_Techniques/Using_the_progressbar_role","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<p class=\"summary\"><span class=\"seoSummary\">This technique demonstrates how to use the <code><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#progressbar\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">progressbar</a></code> role and describes the effect it has on browsers and assistive technology.</span></p>\n\n<p>The <code>progressbar</code> role should be used for an element that displays the progress status for a task that take a long time or consists of several steps.</p>\n\n<p>A progressbar indicates that the user's request has been received and the application is making progress toward completing the requested action. If the actual value of the progressbar can be determined, the developer has to indicate this progress using the <a class=\"property-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuenow\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>aria-valuenow</code></a>, <a class=\"property-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuemin\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>aria-valuemin</code></a>, and <code><a class=\"property-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria/states_and_properties#aria-valuemax\" rel=\" noopener\">aria-valuemax</a> </code>attributes. If the progress value  is indeterminate, the developer should omit the <a class=\"property-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuenow\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>aria-valuenow</code></a> attribute.</p>\n\n<p>As the task progresses, the <code>aria-valuenow</code> value has to be updated dynamically to indicate this progress to assistive technology products. </p>\n\n<p>If the <code>progressbar</code> is describing the loading progress of a particular region of a page, the author <strong class=\"rfc2119\">SHOULD</strong> use <a class=\"property-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-describedby\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>aria-describedby</code></a> to point to the status, and set the <a class=\"state-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-busy\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>aria-busy</code></a> attribute to <code>true</code> on the region until it is finished loading. It is not possible for the user to alter the value of a <code>progressbar</code> because it is always readonly.</p>\n\n<div class=\"note notecard\" id=\"sect1\"><strong>Note:</strong> Assistive technologies generally will render the value of <a class=\"property-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuenow\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>aria-valuenow</code></a> as a percent of the range between the value of <a class=\"property-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuemin\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>aria-valuemin</code></a> and <a class=\"property-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuemax\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>aria-valuemax</code></a>, unless <a class=\"property-reference external\" href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuetext\" rel=\" noopener\"><code>aria-valuetext</code></a> is specified. It is best to set the values for aria-valuemin, aria-valuemax, and aria-valuenow in a manner that is appropriate for this calculation.</div>\n\n<div class=\"note notecard\" id=\"sect2\"><strong>Note:</strong> Elements with the role <code>progressbar</code> have an implicit <code>aria-readonly</code> value of <code>true</code>.</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"possible_effects_on_user_agents_and_assistive_technology","title":"Possible effects on user agents and assistive technology ","isH3":false,"content":"<p>Screen readers should announce the progress updates as they occur. If the progress bar is labeled, the label text should be mentioned as well.</p>\n\n<div class=\"note notecard\" id=\"sect3\"><strong>Note:</strong> Opinions may differ on how assistive technology should handle this. The information provided above is one of those opinions and therefore not normative.</div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_1_basic_progressbar_with_percentage_values","title":"Example 1: Basic progressbar with percentage values","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">role</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>progressbar<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">aria-valuenow</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>20<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">aria-valuemin</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>0<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">aria-valuemax</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>100<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>20 %<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"example_2_using_aria-valuetext","title":"Example 2: Using aria-valuetext ","isH3":true,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>div</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">role</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>progressbar<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">aria-valuenow</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>20<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">aria-valuemin</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>0<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">aria-valuetext</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>Step 2: Copying files... <span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">aria-valuemax</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>100<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n  Step 2: Copying files...\n<span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>div</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"working_examples","title":"Working Examples:","isH3":true,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"notes","title":"Notes ","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"aria_attributes_used","title":"ARIA attributes used","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#progressbar\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">progressbar</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuenow\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">aria-valuenow</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuemin\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">aria-valuemin</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuemax\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">aria-valuemax</a></li>\n\t<li><a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-1.1/#aria-valuetext\" class=\"external\" rel=\" noopener\">aria-valuetext</a></li>\n</ul>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"related_aria_techniques","title":"Related ARIA techniques ","isH3":false,"content":""}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"compatibility","title":"Compatibility","isH3":false,"content":"<p class=\"comment\">TBD: Add support information for common UA and AT product combinations</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"additional_resources","title":"Additional resources","isH3":false,"content":""}}],"toc":[{"text":"Possible effects on user agents and assistive technology ","id":"possible_effects_on_user_agents_and_assistive_technology"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Notes ","id":"notes"},{"text":"ARIA attributes used","id":"aria_attributes_used"},{"text":"Related ARIA techniques ","id":"related_aria_techniques"},{"text":"Compatibility","id":"compatibility"},{"text":"Additional resources","id":"additional_resources"}],"summary":"This technique demonstrates how to use the progressbar role and describes the effect it has on browsers and assistive technology.This technique demonstrates how to use the progressbar role and describes the effect it has on browsers and assistive technology.","popularity":0.0019,"modified":"2022-02-18T09:30:25.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"Utiliser le rôle progressbar","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"progressbar ロールの使